                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.942/17: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Neville</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-07-24T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 24, 1928—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>82. Referring to Peking’s 560, July 23, 6 p.m. It is requested that you cable
                    briefly your comments regarding official reaction in Japan to the Chinese
                    denunciation of the 1896 treaty, and also regarding press reports to the effect
                    that the Japanese Government has warned Marshal Chang against allying with the
                    Nationalist Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
